last_episode_to_air.name: The Inquisition
last_episode_to_air.overview: The students of Elmore Junior High find their world turned upside down when the mysterious school superintendent comes to stamp out their cartoonish ways.

name: The Amazing World of Gumball
overview: The life of Gumball Watterson, a 12-year old cat who attends middle school in Elmore. Accompanied by his pet, adoptive brother, and best friend Darwin Watterson, he frequently finds himself involved in various shenanigans around the city, during which he interacts with various family members: Anais, Richard, and Nicole Watterson, and other various citizens.

seasons.name: Season 1
seasons.overview: The first season of the British-American animated comedy television series The Amazing World of Gumball originally aired from May 3, 2011 and March 13, 2012 on Cartoon Network. Consisting of 36 episodes, the season premiered with the episode "The DVD" and concluded with the episode "The Fight".

seasons.name: Season 2
seasons.overview: The second season of the British-American animated comedy series The Amazing World of Gumball originally aired from August 7, 2012 to December 3, 2013. Consisting of 40 episodes, the season premiered with the episode "The Remote" and concluded with the episode "The Finale."

seasons.name: Season 3
seasons.overview: The third season of the British-American animated comedy series The Amazing World of Gumball premiered on June 5, 2014 in the United States and September 14, 2014 in the United Kingdom. The season will consist of 40 episodes and debuted with the episode "The Kids."

seasons.name: Season 4
seasons.overview: The fourth season of the British-American animated comedy series The Amazing World of Gumball premiered on July 7, 2015 in the United States with the episode "The Return." It will consist of 40 eleven-minute episodes, as were the previous two seasons.

seasons.name: Season 6
seasons.overview: The sixth season was confirmed on June 22, 2016 on Ben Bocquelet's Twitter. Unlike the first five seasons will have 44 episodes. The premiere date of this season was January 5, 2018.

episodes.name: The DVD
episodes.overview: An overdue DVD causes chaos (and a hefty fee) for Gumball and Darwin.

episodes.name: The Responsible
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin get to babysit Anais whilst their parents go to a PTA meeting but being "responsible" has a different meaning when you don't know what it means.

episodes.name: The Third
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin grow bored of one another and seek out a third friend to make their lives more exciting.

episodes.name: The Debt
episodes.overview: Believing that his life had been saved, Gumball vows to repay his debt by saving Mr. Robinson's life.

episodes.name: The End
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin, thinking that the world will end in 24 hours, decide to make the most out of their remaining time.

episodes.name: The Dress
episodes.overview: When his clothes are shrunk in the washing machine by his father, Gumball is forced to wear his mother's wedding dress to school.

episodes.name: The Quest
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin help Anais get her beloved doll back after it is lost on the way to school.

episodes.name: The Spoon
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin become unwitting accomplices in a stick-up at a gas station.

episodes.name: The Pressure
episodes.overview: When Masami claims that Darwin is her boyfriend, Gumball vows to help his friend before he gets kissed.

episodes.name: The Painting
episodes.overview: After seeing a picture that Anais drew, Principal Brown assumes that Anais finds her family dysfunctional, so he begins to meddle in their family life.

episodes.name: The Laziest
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin challenge their father to a laziness competition, with the loser having to do the winner's chores.

episodes.name: The Ghost
episodes.overview: When a ghost named Carrie possesses Gumball's body in order to feel earthly experiences and to eat, he must learn to say "no" to her.

episodes.name: The Mystery
episodes.overview: Gumball decides to investigate when his class finds Principal Brown wrapped up in toilet paper, shaved and, covered in green paint, or else face detention.

episodes.name: The Prank
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin's pranks on their father get out of hand.

episodes.name: The Gi
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin are ridiculed for their martial-arts outfits by their schoolmates, and their mom tries to convince them to take them off.

episodes.name: The Kiss
episodes.overview: A kiss from Grandma JoJo traumatizes Gumball, and Darwin attempts to help him forget.

episodes.name: The Party
episodes.overview: Gumball and his friends are invited to a high-school party hosted by Tobias's sister Rachel, but they must find dates in order to attend.

episodes.name: The Refund
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin go to great lengths to get their money back from an incompatible video game, but the rental store's policy prevents them from getting it.

episodes.name: The Robot
episodes.overview: Gumball decides to help Bobert act like a real boy. However, it soon becomes a battle for his very identity when the robot plots to take over his life.

episodes.name: The Picnic
episodes.overview: A school picnic in the Forest of Doom poses a hazard for Gumball and Darwin.

episodes.name: The Goons
episodes.overview: Gumball competes in a race in order to win Dad back.

episodes.name: The Secret
episodes.overview: Gumball tries desperately to find out Darwin's secret.

episodes.name: The Sock
episodes.overview: Mr. Small teaches Gumball and Darwin various ways of becoming more honest.

episodes.name: The Genius
episodes.overview: Darwin goes to an institute for geniuses.

episodes.name: The Poltergeist
episodes.overview: Richard believes there's a ghost in the attic but is actually Mr. Robinson who Gumball moved up there after entering a catatonic state due to being kicked out by his wife. Gumball and Darwin work on trying to restore Mr. Robinson whilst Richard, unaware of this, sets traps for the ghost.

episodes.name: The Mustache
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin want to become adults, Richard wants to lose weight. After accidentally having their cereal switched with supplements Richard ordered, Gumball, Darwin and Anais find themselves having very unusual growth spurts.

episodes.name: The Date
episodes.overview: Gumball learns how to date, so he can go out on a date with Penny. Later on it turns out that he is going to a funeral, not a date.

episodes.name: The Club
episodes.overview: When Gumball turns down an offer to join the Rejects Club, they seek to enact revenge against him.

episodes.name: The Wand
episodes.overview: The guys share the power of magic with Dad.

episodes.name: The Ape
episodes.overview: Ms. Simian cozies up to Gumball in order to win an award.

episodes.name: The Car
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin are eager enough to do numerous chores at Mr. Robinson's house, until they accidentally destroy his car.

episodes.name: The Curse
episodes.overview: Gumball's good day turns bad to worse throughout his school day, much to the point where he believes he is "cursed".

episodes.name: The Microwave
episodes.overview: Gumball creates a creature, made of every gross thing he could find, with a cannibalistic appetite.

episodes.name: The Meddler
episodes.overview: Seeing Gumball in need of attention, Nicole hangs out with him at school, which becomes increasingly embarrassing for her son.

episodes.name: The Helmet
episodes.overview: Gumball wears a lucky helmet, but it tears his family apart.

episodes.name: The Fight
episodes.overview: After Gumball's bullying problem, Tina Rex demands to have a fight with him.

1.name: Season 1
1.overview: The first season of the British-American animated comedy television series The Amazing World of Gumball originally aired from May 3, 2011 and March 13, 2012 on Cartoon Network. Consisting of 36 episodes, the season premiered with the episode "The DVD" and concluded with the episode "The Fight".

episodes.name: The Remote
episodes.overview: The Watterson family fights over the remote when they realize everything they want to watch comes on at the same time.

episodes.name: The Colossus
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin upset a giant.

episodes.name: The Knights
episodes.overview: Gumball and Tobias compete for Penny's affection by putting on the lamest duel in history.

episodes.name: The Fridge
episodes.overview: Mom tries to inspire Gumball to develop ambition.

episodes.name: The Flower
episodes.overview: Gumball is jealous when he sees Leslie with Penny.

episodes.name: The Banana
episodes.overview: Gumball seeks justice when Banana Joe chews Darwin's pen.

episodes.name: The Phone
episodes.overview: Darwin develops a texting addiction when he and Gumball get their first cell phone.

episodes.name: The Job
episodes.overview: Richard gets a job as a pizza delivery man, which worries Nicole when strange things begin to occur around the neighborhood.

episodes.name: Halloween
episodes.overview: Gumball, Darwin and Anais go to a haunted-house party.

episodes.name: The Treasure
episodes.overview: Anais hunts for hidden treasure after uncovering a secret.

episodes.name: The Apology
episodes.overview: Miss Simian owes Gumball an apology.

episodes.name: The Words
episodes.overview: Darwin tries to be more direct with Gumball as his teacher.

episodes.name: The Skull
episodes.overview: The guys befriend a compulsive liar.

episodes.name: The Bet
episodes.overview: Bobert becomes Gumball's servant and obeys every command he receives.

episodes.name: Christmas
episodes.overview: Santa Claus is coming to town. Unfortunately he gets run over by the Wattersons, so it's up to them to save Christmas.

episodes.name: The Watch
episodes.overview: The guys try to retrieve a family heirloom from an old man.

episodes.name: The Bumpkin
episodes.overview: Gumball envies rural life and asks Idaho to teach his family to live like potatoes.

episodes.name: The Flakers
episodes.overview: Darwin abandons Gumball when faced with a beating by Tina, so Gumball plots revenge.

episodes.name: The Authority
episodes.overview: After Richard is hospitalized from an accident, Granny JoJo is overprotective and puts the family in danger, which leads Nicole to disagree with her parenting style.

episodes.name: The Virus
episodes.overview: An evil virus seeks vengeance on Gumball, Darwin, and Teri after they wipe out his army of bacteria.

episodes.name: The Pony
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin rent a film to watch with Anais, but they keep getting distracted on their way home.

episodes.name: The Hero
episodes.overview: Richard gets upset when he realizes Gumball and Darwin think of him as a laughing stock.

episodes.name: The Dream
episodes.overview: Darwin kisses Penny in one of Gumball's dreams and he gets mad about it.

episodes.name: The Sidekick
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin try to get a game back from Tobias, but Darwin begins to feel like he is just a sidekick to Gumball.

episodes.name: The Photo
episodes.overview: Gumball tries to look good in the school photos.

episodes.name: The Tag
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin get caught in the middle of a trash can feud between Richard and Mr. Robinson.

episodes.name: The Storm
episodes.overview: A plot to improve Alan and Carmen's relationship backfires, and Gumball has to reunite them.

episodes.name: The Lesson
episodes.overview: The guys have detention and try to escape; Granny JoJo is overprotective and puts the family in danger.

episodes.name: The Game
episodes.overview: The Wattersons play Dodge or Dare (Dodj or Daar).

episodes.name: The Limit
episodes.overview: Mom lets the Wattersons have it in a supermarket.

episodes.name: The Voice
episodes.overview: When Gumball and Darwin receive a scary email, everyone is a suspect...

episodes.name: The Promise
episodes.overview: Darwin has promised to play video games with Gumball, but there is a Banana Joe-shaped problem...

episodes.name: The Castle
episodes.overview: When Nicole is away "anything goes" and Richard's lack of rules soon attracts unwelcome house guests.

episodes.name: The Boombox
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin try to understand Juke's urgent beatbox message.

episodes.name: The Tape
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin fail to make instant home movie classics.

episodes.name: The Sweaters
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin's reputation is challenged and they really couldn't care less...

episodes.name: The Internet
episodes.overview: Gumball decides to take down the Internet after he accidentally creates an embarrasing viral web video.

episodes.name: The Plan
episodes.overview: The Watterson kids come up with a fool-proof plan to save Nicole, but is it Gumball-proof?

episodes.name: The World
episodes.overview: The life of the "inanimate" objects of Elmore are shown in a series of short skits.

episodes.name: The Finale
episodes.overview: The Wattersons are surprised to discover that their past actions have consequences.

2.name: Season 2
2.overview: The second season of the British-American animated comedy series The Amazing World of Gumball originally aired from August 7, 2012 to December 3, 2013. Consisting of 40 episodes, the season premiered with the episode "The Remote" and concluded with the episode "The Finale."

episodes.name: The Kids
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin's voices may be breaking, but they're showing no signs of growing up. Whilst Gumball and Darwin make fun of Mom and Dad for being old, their voices start to break. They try to ignore it, but everybody they meet reacts to their new and unpredictable voices.

episodes.name: The Fan
episodes.overview: New Elmore Junior High student Sarah becomes Gumball and Darwin's obsessive number-one fan.

episodes.name: The Coach
episodes.overview: The new coach at Elmore High stands up to Jamie. The new Coach witnesses Jamie bullying the other kids at lunch and steps in. Jamie is made to apologize, much to the amazement of the other kids. Gumball and Darwin worry about Jamie seeking revenge, especially when they see her sneaking into the back of Coach's car.

episodes.name: The Joy
episodes.overview: When Miss Simian sees Gumball and Darwin joyful on Monday, she knows that something is wrong with them. She performs tests on them, but the nurse disapproves what she's doing. But suddenly, Gumball and Darwin start to infect the school with the 'Joy Virus', and it's up to Miss Simian and her tape player to cure the students.

episodes.name: The Puppy
episodes.overview: The Watterson children's long-awaited pet puppy turns out to be a turtle which hates them.

episodes.name: The Recipe
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin discover the secret behind their classmate Anton's immortality.

episodes.name: The Name
episodes.overview: When Mom reveals that Gumball's real name is "Zach," Gumball adopts a cheesy, annoying persona to match the name. His family tries to make him remember the old Gumball, as this new Zach persona is progressively taking over Gumball's life and erasing his memories.

episodes.name: The Extras
episodes.overview: Skits about the random extra characters seen throughout the series.

episodes.name: The Gripes
episodes.overview: When Gumball and Darwin begin to complain about every little thing in their lives, the people of Elmore City mistakenly assumes charity cases and put together a benefit to raise money for them, leaving them having to fix the mix-up.

episodes.name: The Vacation
episodes.overview: While driving to a campground, Nicole tells a horror story, which slowly starts to come true as their car breaks down and a stranger comes to help them out.

episodes.name: The Fraud
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin discover Principal Brown's diploma is fake, and Principal Brown is determined to keep their discovery a secret.

episodes.name: The Void
episodes.overview: When Gumball and Darwin investigate a missing classmate, they discover a far greater mystery... about Elmore.

episodes.name: The Boss
episodes.overview: Mr. Robinson has a stress attack and needs a  stuffing transfusion from his son Rocky the janitor. He won't take it unless Rocky gets a better job in life. Rocky gets one with Chanax, where he becomes a work drone. Gumball and Darwin now need to get Rocky's soul back from his boss in order to get him to surgery.

episodes.name: The Move
episodes.overview: Clayton, a compulsive liar tells Gumball and Darwin about his awesome martial arts move, and discover that he wasn't lying.

episodes.name: The Law
episodes.overview: Doughnut Cop shows Gumball and Darwin that the smallest misdemeanor can lead to a breakdown in law.

episodes.name: The Allergy
episodes.overview: Gumball needs to find a cure for Darwin's allergy before he sneezes Elmore off the map.

episodes.name: The Mothers
episodes.overview: It's Mother's Day and kids put their moms through a series of tests to determine who has the World's Greatest Mom.

episodes.name: The Password
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin are shocked to discover that Anais is Dad's favorite child.

episodes.name: The Procrastinators
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin spend the day doing other things instead of taking out the trash like their mother told them to do before she got back home.

episodes.name: The Shell
episodes.overview: Gumball inadvertently cracks open Penny's shell, and discovers who she really is inside...

episodes.name: The Burden
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin are left in charge of the class pet hamster, Chris Morris, but they end up leaving it at school over the weekend.

episodes.name: The Bros
episodes.overview: Darwin becomes jealous of Gumball and Penny's new relationship and sets out to find information that will break them up.

episodes.name: The Mirror
episodes.overview: Gumball refuses to forward an e-mail purportedly sent by a ghost, against Darwin's advice. When a curse begins to take effect and their family is dragged into another dimension, Gumball and Darwin seek Carrie's help to save them.

episodes.name: The Man
episodes.overview: After Granny Jojo brings her new boyfriend to dinner at the Watterson household, Richard forbids her from seeing the boyfriend again.

episodes.name: The Pizza
episodes.overview: The Wattersons have had a bad day, but it turns out Larry has too and it's about to get worse... for everyone!

episodes.name: The Lie
episodes.overview: Noticing that everyone is in the doldrums of January, Gumball and Anais invent a new holiday to spark excitement.

episodes.name: The Butterfly
episodes.overview: When a Butterfly emerges from its chrysalis Gumball and Darwin want to release it. Miss Simian warns them about the butterfly effect. Gumball releases it anyways, and a domino effect causes chaos throughout the city.

episodes.name: The Question
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin try to figure out the meaning of life after coming down from a sugar rush.

episodes.name: The Saint
episodes.overview: After failing at making Alan lose his temper, Gumball and Darwin decide to adopt Alan's positive attitude.

episodes.name: The Friend
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin help Anais make up an imaginary friend who turns out to be all too real.

episodes.name: The Oracle
episodes.overview: After discovering a prophetic painting depicting Gumball's naked run through the mall, he is determined to avoid that outcome.

episodes.name: The Safety
episodes.overview: Darwin becomes obsessed with safety after seeing a video in class.

episodes.name: The Society
episodes.overview: Gumball is convinced there is a Secret Society in school, and he wants in.

episodes.name: The Spoiler
episodes.overview: When Gumball and Darwin have to wait to see a movie, they must go an entire week without someone spoiling the plot.

episodes.name: The Countdown
episodes.overview: Miss Simian threatens to expel the boys if they are late for school, so they race a clock in order to arrive on time.

episodes.name: The Nobody
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin investigate the disappearance  of the family's stuff only to find out some stranger is living in the house with them.

episodes.name: The Downer
episodes.overview: When Gumball's family tries to cheer him out of an inexplicable lousy mood, he wishes they would all disappear.

episodes.name: The Egg
episodes.overview: Nicole wants to show to Felicity that the Wattersons are a normal family, while her son, Billy, meets Anais.

episodes.name: The Triangle
episodes.overview: Gumball grows jealous of Darwin's new talent.

episodes.name: The Money
episodes.overview: The Wattersons become poor when Richard loses all their money.

3.name: Season 3
3.overview: The third season of the British-American animated comedy series The Amazing World of Gumball premiered on June 5, 2014 in the United States and September 14, 2014 in the United Kingdom. The season will consist of 40 episodes and debuted with the episode "The Kids."

episodes.name: The Return
episodes.overview: Richard tries to find the kids before Nicole realizes they're gone.

episodes.name: The Nemesis
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin discover that Rob, who once swore to wreak vengeance on them, has been trying to destroy them for some time… but his traps never work.

episodes.name: The Crew
episodes.overview: When Gumball and Darwin decide to join a crew, they are determined to prove their worth to senior citizens.

episodes.name: The Others
episodes.overview: After learning what grade Anais is in, Gumball and Darwin learn that there is a whole new world of students.

episodes.name: The Signature
episodes.overview: When Richard learns of Granny Jojo's plans to marry, he sets out to adopt Louie so he can forbid the wedding.

episodes.name: The Check
episodes.overview: Gumball, Darwin and Anais are delighted when Grandpa Louie gives them a check for $5000, but the family soon fights over how to spend it.

episodes.name: The Pest
episodes.overview: When they find Anais training herself for a brutal showdown, Gumball and Darwin realise that their sister is being pestered at school by an annoying kid: Billy. They try to teach her how to resolve the problem peacefully, but Billy has other ideas.

episodes.name: The Sale
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin are crushed to learn that Mr. Robinson is selling his house and moving away, and when trying to make their final moments together last doesn't work, the duo decide to sabotage the sale.

episodes.name: The Gift
episodes.overview: After they receive an extravagant invitation to Masami's birthday party, Gumball and Darwin are anxious to find just the right gift for her. However, they're not the only ones: it turns out every kid in Elmore is competing to get Masami the perfect present.

episodes.name: The Parking
episodes.overview: When the Wattersons arrive at the mall for a day of shopping, they struggle to find a space in the parking lot. They search for a space everywhere -- using all their intelligence, cunning and trickery -- but as the day goes on, the desperate hunt for a space becomes more important than the trip to the mall itself.

episodes.name: The Routine
episodes.overview: Richard's trip to the store to find mayonnaise for the family's burger night turns into a Neverending Story-meets-Conan the Barbarian-style quest where he squares off against Tina Rex's father, Mr. Rex.

episodes.name: The Upgrade
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin upgrade Bobert the robot – and discover that his new operating system is full of buggy and useless applications and is prone to crashing.

episodes.name: The Comic
episodes.overview: Sarah creates a comic of Gumball as a superhero named LaserHeart, prompting Gumball to act like one in real life.

episodes.name: The Romantic
episodes.overview: Fearing that she may be sick of him due to a missing emoji on her message to him, Gumball sends Penny on a romantic quest to rekindle their love, which turns into a disaster when Penny gets lost in the woods.

episodes.name: The Uploads
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin get hooked on watching Elmore Stream (the show's version of YouTube) and viewers get a look at the different online videos the residents of Elmore have uploaded on the Internet.

episodes.name: The Apprentice
episodes.overview: Gumball tags along with Patrick Fitzgerald (Penny's father) as Patrick prepares to pitch plans for a new hospital to the CEO of Chanax -- and ends up roping him into a golf game with the CEO.

episodes.name: The Hug
episodes.overview: To prove to Darwin that he can be unpredictable, Gumball decides to hug the first person he sees -- an anthropomorphic hot dog -- and Gumball ends up in over his head when he and the Hot Dog Guy can't stop bumping into each other.

episodes.name: The Wicked
episodes.overview: After being framed for feeding coffee- and prune juice-laced nuts to the squirrels, Darwin tries to prove to Gumball that Mr. Robinson's wife, Margaret, is a good person underneath her destructive, sociopathic tendencies, but when Darwin sees just how evil Margaret is, the duo decide to catch her committing grand theft auto.

episodes.name: The Traitor
episodes.overview: When Alan allegedly ditches Gumball's dinner date with him, Gumball is desperate to track him down and make him pay for his betrayal, only to learn that Alan is taking his mother, Jessica, to the hospital for an organ transplant.

episodes.name: The Origins (1)
episodes.overview: In this, the first half-hour episode, a four-year-old Gumball becomes too much for young parents, Nicole and Richard, to handle, so they buy him a goldfish, but after the first six die from neglect, stupidity, and unfortunate incidents, Richard finds a special one in a shady red van who bonds with Gumball on a spiritual level. This gets put to the test when Darwin gets flushed down the toilet and must traverse a scary, new world to return home.

episodes.name: The Origins (2)
episodes.overview: In this, the first half-hour episode, a four-year-old Gumball becomes too much for young parents, Nicole and Richard, to handle, so they buy him a goldfish, but after the first six die from neglect, stupidity, and unfortunate incidents, Richard finds a special one in a shady red van who bonds with Gumball on a spiritual level. This gets put to the test when Darwin gets flushed down the toilet and must traverse a scary, new world to return home.

episodes.name: The Girlfriend
episodes.overview: After seeing Alan and Carmen bond during her lunchtime bullying, Jamie decides that she needs a sweetheart... and has her eyes on Darwin.

episodes.name: The Advice
episodes.overview: Mr. Small feels that he hasn't inspired the children of Elmore Junior High, so Gumball and Darwin try to lift his spirits... and end up causing chaos and putting most of the students (and faculty) in the school infirmary (and others in the hospital) after following Mr. Small's useless advice.

episodes.name: The Signal
episodes.overview: Gumball develops a strange stutter, and it makes him accidentally offend Darwin.

episodes.name: The Parasite
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin read Anais' diary and discover her relationship with a new friend is one-sided.

episodes.name: The Love
episodes.overview: The people of Elmore search for the meaning of love.

episodes.name: The Awkwardness
episodes.overview: Gumball is walking in the same direction as Hot Dog Guy, and with each step it becomes increasingly awkward.

episodes.name: The Nest
episodes.overview: A neighbor disappears and the Wattersons investigate, but discover the culprit may be their Evil Turtle.

episodes.name: The Points
episodes.overview: In order for Tobias to let them use his points in a video game, Gumball and Darwin must do his chores for him.

episodes.name: The Bus
episodes.overview: Rocky convinces the kids that they do not have to go to school. However, unbeknownst to the kids, some adults are trying to teach them about skipping school.

episodes.name: The Night
episodes.overview: The Moon examines dreams and nightmares of Elmore residents.

episodes.name: The Misunderstandings
episodes.overview: On his way to a date with Penny, Gumball finds himself dealing with people at their most oblivious.

episodes.name: The Roots
episodes.overview: The family tries to make Darwin connect with his fish roots.

episodes.name: The Blame
episodes.overview: After Felicity bans video games in Elmore, Gumball and his friends try to have books banned instead.

episodes.name: The Slap
episodes.overview: Tobias offends Gumball when he doesn't slap him on the butt.

episodes.name: The Detective
episodes.overview: When Daisy goes missing, Anais suspects Gumball and Darwin.

episodes.name: The Fury
episodes.overview: A strange figure arrives and insults Nicole, but the kids are surprised when Nicole doesn't fight back.

episodes.name: The Compilation
episodes.overview: Odd internet clips are recalled by the people of Elmore.

episodes.name: The Scam
episodes.overview: Gumball scares the school into thinking a monster named Gargaroth is haunting the place, then recruits Carrie and Darwin (who has a crush on Carrie) as ghost exterminators in order to scam everyone in Elmore of their candy.

episodes.name: The Disaster
episodes.overview: Rob gets new powers through a remote control and tries to destroy Gumball's world.

4.name: Season 4
4.overview: The fourth season of the British-American animated comedy series The Amazing World of Gumball premiered on July 7, 2015 in the United States with the episode "The Return." It will consist of 40 eleven-minute episodes, as were the previous two seasons.

episodes.name: The Stories
episodes.overview: Fed up with having to listen to Molly's long, tedious anecdotes, Gumball and Darwin try to teach her how to make them sound more exciting. When this doesn't work, they decide their only option is to give Molly a story worth telling.

episodes.name: The Re-Run
episodes.overview: In this sequel to last season's "The Disaster", Gumball travels back to the events of the previous episode to prevent Rob from ruining his life, but everything he does makes things worse.

episodes.name: The Guy
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin are wary of Anais' new friend, Josh, making her question his motives as well.

episodes.name: The Boredom
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin search for adventure during a walk around Elmore.

episodes.name: The Vision
episodes.overview: After finding a secret manifesto on Alan's memory stick, Gumball and Darwin decide to foil his plan for world domination.

episodes.name: The Choices
episodes.overview: Nicole reminisces about how she met Richard during a disastrous family dinner, and how things could have turned out for her if she had not.

episodes.name: The Code
episodes.overview: The family goes without wi-fi after Mr. Robinson changes the passcode, so Gumball tries to recover it.

episodes.name: The Test
episodes.overview: When he is labeled a "loser" in an online test, Gumball believes he must do the opposite of everything he would normally do. Meanwhile, Darwin and Sarah notice Tobias is stealing Gumball's life and role in the series in the form of a cheesy sitcom.

episodes.name: The Slide
episodes.overview: Rocky decides to stop living life online, and find love on a dating app, and Gumball and Darwin try to help him.

episodes.name: The Loophole
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin give Bobert instructions so he will behave in a safe and responsible manner, but he applies his logic to their rules.

episodes.name: The Potato
episodes.overview: When Darwin has lunch with Idaho, he decides to stop eating potatoes in solidarity with his brotato, but he finds his obsession with his favorite food harder to kick than he ever imagined, so Gumball decides to help his friend curb his carb cravings.

episodes.name: The Fuss
episodes.overview: Nicole tries, and fails, to hide her disappointment when Richard and the kids fail to remember her special day. Richard has to figure out what special day he has actually forgotten and then make it a day to remember or else.

episodes.name: The Copycats
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin are confused when they meet Chi Chi and Ribbit, a pair of siblings that copy everything they do and say. Then they find out this copycat family is making money online from imitating the Watterson family.

episodes.name: The Outside
episodes.overview: The family goes to visit Richard's dad. Based on his basic living standards and extended absence from Richard's life, they assume Frankie must have done a stretch in the slammer.

episodes.name: The Vase
episodes.overview: Sick of Granny Jojo's ugly gifts, Nicole encourages the kids to take matters into their own hands and "accidentally" break her latest hideous vase. But when Gumball, Darwin, and Anais try to destroy it, they discover it is more robust than it seems.

episodes.name: The Matchmaker
episodes.overview: Gumball enlists Carrie to help bring Darwin and Teri together, but when they can't make Darwin and Teri's love blossom naturally, they decide to make it happen supernaturally.

episodes.name: The Box
episodes.overview: The Wattersons receive an unmarked package in the mail. To distract themselves from the urge to open it they all take turns to imagine what it might contain.

episodes.name: The Console
episodes.overview: When Gumball is given a cursed video game console, Elmore becomes trapped inside a fantasy RPG world. Gumball, Darwin and Anais have to battle their way through town, unraveling the secrets of their new virtual reality.

episodes.name: The Ollie
episodes.overview: Gumball teaches Darwin everything he knows about the world of skateboarding.

episodes.name: The Catfish
episodes.overview: When Gumball and Darwin realize Grandpa Louie has no friends, they create one called Muriel, when Granny Jojo finds out Louie has been spending time online with another woman, Muriel not existing is not going to stop her from being destroyed.

episodes.name: The Cycle
episodes.overview: Gumball, Darwin and Anais discover that Mr. Wilson has been picking on Richard for most of his life; ever since he humiliated Richard with a high school prank. The kids try to work their dad through it, but when their efforts fail they realize that getting back at Mr. Wilson is the only way to break the cycle.

episodes.name: The Stars
episodes.overview: When Richard gives Larry’s hairdresser a bad review for saying he’s bald, he gets offered a free haircut. This inspires Gumball and Darwin to go on a reviewing spree across town, forcing Larry to give them stuff with the threat of a bad review. But, just because the customer is always right doesn’t mean that what they’re doing isn’t wrong.

episodes.name: The Grades
episodes.overview: When a failed test grade brings down Gumball’s grade point average, he is forced to return to kindergarten.

episodes.name: The Diet
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin find out why Richard's diet wasn't working, and after they help him lose weight, he becomes more obnoxious.

episodes.name: The Ex
episodes.overview: When Gumball learns that his nemesis, Rob, has found a new nemesis, he tries to sabotage Rob's new "enemy-ship", much to the frustration of Penny.

episodes.name: The Sorcerer
episodes.overview: Gumball refuses to accept he is the only kid at school that does not have special powers. He convinces Mrs. Jötunheim, Hector's mom, to take him on as her apprentice but she soon learns leaving Gumball unsupervised around magic is a big mistake.

episodes.name: The Menu
episodes.overview: The prize jewel on the Secret Joyful Burger menu is a mysterious burger, but to order it you need to know its name. When Larry refuses to tell Richard, Gumball, and Darwin what it is called, they go to super-sized lengths to discover it.

episodes.name: The Uncle
episodes.overview: When Gumball finds out that Ocho has an uncle named Mario, he becomes desperate to meet him.

episodes.name: The Weirdo
episodes.overview: When they see the school bullies making fun of Sussie, Gumball and Darwin decide to try and help her act less weird. They carefully observe her behavior and decide that the only thing they have to change is absolutely everything.

episodes.name: The Heist
episodes.overview: Richard discovers that going into a bank whilst wearing a motorcycle helmet can lead to trouble.

episodes.name: The Singing
episodes.overview: Join the citizens of Elmore for a song and dance spectacular that will have people covering their ears with joy.

episodes.name: The Best
episodes.overview: No matter what Gumball does, Carmen thinks she knows better; when Gumball attempts to gain the moral high ground, but fails, his only option left is to bring Carmen down to his level.

episodes.name: The Worst
episodes.overview: The Wattersons compete over who has the worst life.

episodes.name: The Deal
episodes.overview: Richard goes on strike to prove that his work around the house is under appreciated by Nicole.

episodes.name: The Petals
episodes.overview: When Leslie's petals begin falling off, he feels like his good looks are fading, so Gumball and Darwin use everything they know about style and beauty to try and help him.

episodes.name: The Puppets
episodes.overview: Darwin is delighted when they discover their old childhood toys, but soon realizes that some things are best left in the past.

episodes.name: The Nuisance
episodes.overview: The Wattersons fear the worst when they are summoned to a Town Hall meeting, but are surprised when they're offered a new house - until they discover it's in a different state.

episodes.name: The Line
episodes.overview: The Wattersons will do whatever it takes to get into the first screening of the latest Stellar Odyssey sequel.

episodes.name: The List
episodes.overview: When the kids find out that Mom's life hasn't panned out as she'd hoped, they start taking on her chores, but they accidentally grab her bucket list instead of her to-do list.

episodes.name: The News
episodes.overview: From police chases to the inside scoop on Daisy the Donkey, Channel 6 Elmore News has all the top local stories. Experienced newscaster Kip Schlezinger brings the latest news, sports and weather, even when there is absolutely nothing to report.

episodes.name: The Rival
episodes.overview: When Anais is a newborn baby, Gumball and Darwin become jealous of their new sibling, and spark a baby war.

episodes.name: The Lady
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin find out that Dad has been dressing as a woman to make friends.

episodes.name: The Sucker
episodes.overview: Darwin ends up in detention with Julius, who decides to make Darwin his new target. However, it backfires when Darwin ruins his life.

episodes.name: The Vegging
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin want to veg out all day, but their plans go awry and they have to save the rest of the family.

episodes.name: The One
episodes.overview: Tobias tries to be Gumball’s best friend.

episodes.name: The Father
episodes.overview: The kids try to help Richard bond with Frankie.

episodes.name: The Cringe
episodes.overview: Gumball and Hot Dog Guy discover why they're so awkward with each other.

episodes.name: The Cage
episodes.overview: The kids convince Mr. Corneille to become a cage fighter and set up a fight against a fearsome Russian fighter.

episodes.name: The Faith
episodes.overview: Alan has lost faith in humanity and turns the world black and white. Gumball must get over his hatred of Alan to bring the color back by singing.

episodes.name: The Candidate
episodes.overview: A group of kids get locked in the school after their parents have a charity gala. They appoint Gumball as leader to get them out but it leads to chaos.

episodes.name: The Anybody
episodes.overview: When Clayton shapeshifts into Gumball to take his detention, he starts framing others for misdemeanors so Gumball and Darwin must track Clayton down to stop him.

episodes.name: The Pact
episodes.overview: Gumball and Principal Brown make a pact to tell each other what problems their girlfriends have.

episodes.name: The Neighbor
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin try to find out the name of their neighbor, Antlers Guy, but accidentally blow his witness protection cover.

episodes.name: The Shippening
episodes.overview: Sarah finds a notebook from the Awesome Store which magically makes what she draws happen. Unfortunately, she draws bizarre love stories throughout Elmore.

episodes.name: The Brain
episodes.overview: The Wattersons have to stop doing stupid things in order to prevent Anais from falling into a coma from facepalming too much.

episodes.name: The Parents
episodes.overview: Nicole and her parents reconnect after a long forced absence.

episodes.name: The Founder
episodes.overview: Richard creates chaos in the Chanax building when he is mistaken for the long lost CEO. Nicole and a disgruntled employee must save everyone from Richard's dangerous ideas.

episodes.name: The Schooling
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin take on Larry's jobs for 5 minutes and realize how bad it is.

episodes.name: The Intelligence
episodes.overview: Technology reaches human intelligence then becomes dysfunctional as it picks up human flaws.

episodes.name: The Potion
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin use a magic potion to shrink Hector.

episodes.name: The Spinoffs
episodes.overview: Rob creates a variety of spinoff Elmore shows and formats to replace Gumball.

episodes.name: The Transformation
episodes.overview: Gumball is asked to settle a dispute between Penny and her family.

episodes.name: The Understanding
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin get into trouble misunderstanding a new kid in school.

episodes.name: The Ad
episodes.overview: The Wattersons are forced to rent their house to a pair of elderly fainting goats.

episodes.name: The Ghouls
episodes.overview: Halloween isn't what it used to be. Can Gumball and Darwin help the ghouls get their scare back?

episodes.name: The Stink
episodes.overview: Mr. Small goes feral after Gumball and Darwin expose his hypocrisy.

episodes.name: The Awareness
episodes.overview: Gumball decides to engross himself in plant culture to appease Leslie after making an offensive comment.

episodes.name: The Slip
episodes.overview: Richard misses a package and is forced into an escalating feud with the delivery guy.

episodes.name: The Drama
episodes.overview: Gumball tries to protect Darwin from his unsuitable undead girlfriend Carrie.

episodes.name: The Buddy
episodes.overview: Anais and Jamie form an unlikely partnership when they're accused of a crime they didn't commit.

episodes.name: The Possession
episodes.overview: Richard becomes supernaturally attached to his old refrigerator.

episodes.name: The Master
episodes.overview: The Wattersons play a fantasy role-playing board game to resolve their differences.

episodes.name: The Silence
episodes.overview: Have Gumball and Darwin finally run out of things to say to each other?

episodes.name: The Future
episodes.overview: Banana Joe's Mom can predict the future, but she can't predict her own disappearance.

episodes.name: The Wish
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin believe they've turned Miss Simian into a neck-cushion.

episodes.name: The Factory
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin save the day at the Rainbow Factory.

episodes.name: The Agent
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin's clothes go missing after a swimming lesson; when Gumball is forced to wear a tuxedo from the lost and found office, he believes it makes him look like a certain dapper British secret agent.

episodes.name: The Web
episodes.overview: Gumball and Darwin realize that the adult residents of Elmore are dangerously naive when it comes to being safe online, and in fact are in serious need of the boys' help with even the simplest of tasks.

episodes.name: The Mess
episodes.overview: After staying up all night, the boys baby-sit Penny's little sister and manage to lose her in the blink of an eye.

episodes.name: The Heart
episodes.overview: Mr. Robinson tries and repeatedly fails to win back Gumball and Darwin's friendship.

episodes.name: The Revolt
episodes.overview: Darwin tries to highlight the plight of all the household objects he feels are being oppressed and maltreated by the uncaring residents of Elmore, then decides to lead those objects in a revolt against the townspeople.

episodes.name: The Decisions
episodes.overview: When everything goes wrong in Darwin's life, he begins to suspect that Gumball's bad influence might be to blame; Darwin decides to go elsewhere for guidance and finds a new mentor in Alan.

episodes.name: The BFFs
episodes.overview: When Gumball's old BFF Fuzzy turns up on his doorstep, Darwin struggles to accept that there was someone before him and fails to contain his jealousy.

episodes.name: The Inquisition
episodes.overview: The students of Elmore Junior High find their world turned upside down when the mysterious school superintendent comes to stamp out their cartoonish ways.

6.name: Season 6
6.overview: The sixth season was confirmed on June 22, 2016 on Ben Bocquelet's Twitter. Unlike the first five seasons will have 44 episodes. The premiere date of this season was January 5, 2018.
